<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Soak the beans overnight, change the water and bring to violent boil, 10 mins. Change the water and cook with bicarbonate 45 mins to 75 mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Force through a sieve, then put beans and liquid through muslin and squeeze out water]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[cook with sugar until mixed in and glossy. when done add a pinch of salt and mix well]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Whiz egg and water in food processor. Add flour, cornstarch, and oil and whizz until you get a thin batter. Let stand for 10 mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Mix the frying oils, and smear 1/5 over a hot pan, rubbing with paper towel. Pour 1/5 of batter in and swirl to make a pancake]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[After 30 secs spread 1/5 bean paste over centre of pancake, fold sides over it, flatten with spatulla, and cook another 20 secs, turn over and cook another 30 s]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Repeat for remaining 4 pancakes]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Slice, dust sugar over the top, and serve hot or cold. You can also dust sesame seeds over it or kinako]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
